Source: bootcontrol
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: BootControl Contributors <maintainers@bootcontrol.local>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), cargo, dpkg-dev (>= 1.17.14)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/SzymonPaczos/BootControl

Package: bootcontrol
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Modern, memory-safe bootloader manager for Linux (User space)
 BootControl replaces tools like Grub Customizer with a secure,
 declarative, and auditable alternative.
 .
 This package provides the CLI and TUI frontends for managing boot targets,
 running as an unprivileged user and talking to the D-Bus daemon.

Package: bootcontrold
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libdbus-1-3, policykit-1
Description: Modern, memory-safe bootloader manager for Linux (Daemon)
 BootControl replaces tools like Grub Customizer with a secure,
 declarative, and auditable alternative.
 .
 This package provides the privileged daemon that performs actual operations
 on the bootloader configuration, protected via Polkit authorization and ETags.
